  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt; By reason of inadequate outlook, low levels of daylight/sunlight, lack of privacy, and the absence of private outdoor amenity space, the proposal results in an unacceptable \r\nstandard of residential accommodation. As such, the proposed development is \r\ncontrary to &lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a351920f-7fff-0040-b588-fac329402276&quot;&gt;Policy LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan (LP33) (2020), the Greater London Authority Housing SPG, London Plan (2021) policy D6 (including relevant Table 3.1), and Technical Housing Standards-Nationally Described Space Standards (2015).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The\r\n proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure \r\ncar-free development, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable \r\nmodes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the\r\n surrounding area, contrary to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;policy T6 (Car Parking) of the \r\nLondon Plan (2021) and policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of\r\n Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning \r\nContributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a\r\n contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum \r\nreasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to \r\npolicy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), \r\npolicy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and\r\n Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.2;text-align: justify;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;&quot; id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-31c65958-7fff-f96b-1c6d-494e24e92936&quot;&gt;The development provides no secure or sheltered on-site cycle parking provision. In the absence of cycle parking the proposal fails to adequately promote sustainable transport. As such, the proposal fails to comply with policy LP42 of the Hackney Local Plan (LP33) (2020) and p&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;olicy T5 (Cycling), and Table 10.2 of the London Plan (2021).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
